main event: A bright, circular disc-like object was observed moving rapidly and silently across the sky in Atlanta, Georgia on October 28, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as moving at speeds between 12-25, though the exact distance could not be estimated.
Multiple witnesses observed the object, though it is unclear if they all saw it continuously.
The object made a strange, high-pitched whining noise and had a bright reddish color.
The object appeared to suddenly speed up and disappear from view.
This was not the first time the witness had seen a similar sphere of light passing overhead in the past year.
